Test Procedures: Integration Procedures for Unit Testing

An Integration Procedure that performs a unit test is a Test Procedure. You can use a Test Procedure to unit test almost anything an Integration Procedure can invoke.

Using Test Procedures and the test framework, you can:

Provide sample input to the entity being tested using a Set Values for Integration Procedures component.

Mock responses of specific steps if the entity being tested is an Integration Procedure.

Compare expected and actual results using an Assert Action for Integration Procedures component.

Test Procedures are rolled back after finishing, so they don't affect the database.

When testing another Integration Procedure, you can mock components to simulate their responses. For example, you can mock a credit score lookup.

To mock a component that returns a single value, specify a Key/Value pair under Mock Responses Map in the Procedure Configuration.

To mock a component with a complex response, edit the mockResponseMap node as JSON.

The following component types must be mocked:

* DocuSign Envelope Action for Integration Procedures (response to delivered email not available)
* Email Action for Integration Procedures (response to delivered email not available)
* HTTP Action for Integration Procedures (Salesforce testing requirements)

When a Test Procedure or an Integration Procedure being tested includes a Remote Action with an HTTP callout, enclose the callout in an if statement to prevent it from running during tests.

A Workflow example tests a calculation performed by another Integration Procedure.
title: Unit Testing with OmniStudio Integration Procedures
